  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode 1db4baa6), kernel_verified on the first attempt. Picked as a fresh gap in the domain's 'finite sums/products' focus: the domain already has gauss_sum/sum_squares/sum_cubes (degree 1/2/3 power sums) and arith_seq_sum (general arithmetic series, division-free via a *2 factor) but nothing at the 'sum of triangular numbers' level -- this is the natural next rung, using the same division-avoidance trick (multiply through by 3, here matching the true denominator of n(n+1)(n+2)/6 once the implicit factor of 2 from (k+1)(k+2)=2*T_(k+1) is accounted for). Confirmed no existing packet duplicates this via `grep -rl triangular\\|tetrahedral packets/elementary/*/*.json` (no hits) before authoring. Domain tagged `algebra` per this folder's established convention (schema has no `induction` domain value; see `exists_prime_factorization`'s notes from the same cycle for the same finding).",
